    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "That's not a node editor.  That is a new medium",
      "uuid": "178a80cd90644c24b3d00c2f7afa8ce1",
      "x": -1025.4099562839324,
      "y": 49.96339647876454,
      "width": 501.0545528166878,
      "height": 30.601315281210645,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "That's not a node editor.  That is a new medium",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "654d8caf0a21459fb54a0a797cd66035",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The bug is in `_clear`. `QGraphicsItem` itself has a `data(key)` method, so `hasattr(item, 'data')` is `True` for **every** item in the scene \u2014 including Port ellipses, which also have `rect()` from `QGraphicsEllipseItem`. Every probe hits a port and returns `False`, so nothing ever spawns.\n\nFix: check `isinstance` against `BaseNode` instead:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "3df3a6200355419a8958f37cce45bee2",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 372.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The root cause: `QGraphicsItem.data(key)` is a Qt method that exists on every graphics item, so `hasattr(item, 'data')` was `True` for ports, wires, everything \u2014 and `QGraphicsEllipseItem` (which ports extend) also has `rect()`. Every probe hit a port and blocked. `isinstance(item, BaseNode)` only matches actual canvas nodes.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
